wet or dry
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:an early workers' expression indicating that wages should be paid whether the weather is wet (and no work can be done) or dry
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
